  "text": "Found several categories of sensitive content that should be cleaned up before public release:\n\n### High Priority - Internal/Personal References:\n1. **fsck.com** - Private domain for app distribution\n   - In CI/CD workflow (.github/workflows/ci.yml)\n   - In build scripts (scripts/build-macos-app.ts)\n   - In documentation (docs/SPARKLE-SETUP.md)\n   - Should be replaced with placeholder or generic hosting reference\n\n2. **Dropbox Setup Documentation** - Contains sensitive workflow instructions\n   - docs/SPARKLE-SETUP.md - Full Dropbox setup guide with credential instructions\n   - Scripts for managing Dropbox tokens (scripts/get-dropbox-urls.ts)\n   - References to personal Dropbox app folder setup\n\n3. **GitHub Actions Secrets & Personal Details**\n   - CI workflow references 'obra' user specifically (line 36: `github.actor == 'obra'`)\n   - References to personal Apple ID and deployment credentials\n   - SSH deployment to jessie@fsck.com (line 427)\n\n4. **.private-journal directory**\n   - Already commented out in .gitignore (line 106: `#.private-journal/`)\n   - But IS currently committed in the repo\n   - Contains personal notes/decisions (e.g., 2025-09-13 entry about hiring)\n\n### Medium Priority - Implementation Details:\n1. **Private key management** (docs/SPARKLE-SETUP.md)\n   - References to `sparkle_private_key` file and EdDSA signing\n   - Should clarify this is for maintainer use only\n\n2. **macOS app build infrastructure**\n   - Specific Apple Developer credentials handling\n   - Notarization process references\n\n### Low Priority - Code Comments:\n- Standard TypeScript `private` keyword usage in code (not sensitive)\n- Generic TODO/FIXME comments without personal details",
